heating /ˈhiːtɪŋ/

1. N-UNCOUNT Heating is the process of heating a building or room, considered especially from the point of view of how much this costs. 供暖 

例： We wanted to reduce the cost of heating and air-conditioning. 我们想减少供暖与空调的开支。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Heating is the system and equipment that is used to heat a building. 供暖系统和设备 

例： I wish I knew how to turn on the heating. 要是我知道如何打开暖气装置就好了。 

